# Two-model setup (build both):
#
#   The CODER (fast default, for bulk/agentic loops) — Qwen3-Coder 30B-A3B, 64K ctx:
#     printf 'FROM qwen3-coder:30b\nPARAMETER num_ctx 65536\n' | ollama create qwen3-coder-64k -f -
#
#   The THINKER (on-demand, for hard reasoning) — Qwen3.6 35B-A3B, 64K ctx — this file:
#     ollama create qwen3.6-64k -f Modelfile
#
# Qwen3.6 is a hybrid reasoning model: it "thinks" by default (slower, ~18 tok/s,
# verbose), which is what we want from the thinker. Note: a `SYSTEM /no_think`
# directive does NOT reliably suppress it — only the runtime flag `--think=false`
# (or pi's reasoning:false) does. So we keep thinking ON here and use qwen3-coder
# for the fast path instead.
FROM qwen3.6:35b-a3b
PARAMETER num_ctx 65536
